cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GT 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with capturing materials from a single image. Additionally, the use of deep learning methods further supports this categorization. 

The paper may also belong to the Graphics (cs.GR) sub-category as it involves rendering and re-rendering images to measure quality. 

The use of deep networks for training data suggests that the paper may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. 

The paper's focus on capturing spatially varying materials suggests that it may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. 

Finally, the use of image re-renderings as a measure of quality suggests that the paper may also belong to the Game Theory (cs.GT) sub-category.
